Package: macemu-webrtc
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: Classic Macintosh emulation with WebRTC streaming
 BasiliskII and SheepShaver emulators with browser-based streaming support.
 .
 Features:
  - Stream classic Mac OS (System 7, Mac OS 8, Mac OS 9) to web browsers
  - Multiple video codecs: H.264, AV1, VP9, PNG, WebP
  - Low-latency audio streaming via Opus
  - WebRTC-based peer-to-peer streaming
  - Dirty rectangle optimization for still-image codecs
  - Browser-based UI with configuration management
 .
 This package includes:
  - BasiliskII (68k Mac emulator)
  - SheepShaver (PowerPC Mac emulator)
  - WebRTC streaming server
  - Web-based client interface
 .
 After installation, run 'macemu-webrtc-setup' to initialize your environment.
